## Authentication

{{#if showOAuth2}}
### OAuth2

To connect to this MCP server, obtain an OAuth2 access token from the token endpoint:

{{#if subscriptionPlans.length}}
1. Register or use an existing application in the developer portal.
2. Subscribe to this MCP server under your application.
3. Generate OAuth2 keys (client credentials) for your application.
4. Exchange your client credentials for an access token:
   ```
   POST {{#if tokenEndpoint}}{{tokenEndpoint}}{{else}}<tokenEndpoint>{{/if}}
   Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
   grant_type=client_credentials&client_id=<clientId>&client_secret=<clientSecret>
   ```
5. Include the token in the Authorization header:
   ```
   Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
   ```
{{else}}
1. Register or use an existing application in the developer portal.
2. Generate OAuth2 keys (client credentials) for your application.
3. Exchange your client credentials for an access token:
   ```
   POST {{#if tokenEndpoint}}{{tokenEndpoint}}{{else}}<tokenEndpoint>{{/if}}
   Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
   grant_type=client_credentials&client_id=<clientId>&client_secret=<clientSecret>
   ```
4. Include the token in the Authorization header:
   ```
   Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
   ```
{{/if}}

{{/if}}
{{#if showApiKey}}
### API Key

To connect to this MCP server using an API key:

{{#if subscriptionPlans.length}}
1. Register or use an existing application in the developer portal.
2. Subscribe to this MCP server under your application.
3. Generate an API key for your application.
4. Include the key in the request header:
   ```
   api-key: <your-api-key>
   ```
{{else}}
1. Register or use an existing application in the developer portal.
2. Generate an API key for your application.
